President Biden has declared a major disaster in the State of Alaska due to severe storms, flooding, landslides, and mudslides that occurred from November 30 to December 2, 2020. This declaration allows federal assistance to supplement state and local recovery efforts. Federal funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Thomas J. Dargan has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Further designations may be made based on damage assessments. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.